    "faq":  {
                "title":  "Frequently Asked Questions",
                "subtitle":  "Everything you need to know about deposits, plans, pools, and withdrawals.",
                "q1":  "How do I deposit USDT?",
                "q1a":  "Go to Dashboard → Deposit, choose your network (ERC20, BEP20, or TRC20), and send USDT to your address. Deposits are detected automatically in most cases.",
                "q2":  "What is the difference between solo and shared plans?",
                "q2a":  "Solo plans start immediately after purchase. Shared plans collect contributions from multiple users until the target is reached, then activate together with profit split by contribution share.",
                "q3":  "When do I receive daily profit?",
                "q3a":  "Profits accrue live throughout the day and are credited at midnight (server time). You can see accruing profit on your dashboard in real time.",
                "q4":  "Can I withdraw my deposit balance?",
                "q4a":  "No. Only credited profit can be withdrawn. Your deposit balance is used for plan purchases and is returned as principal when your plan completes.",
                "q5":  "How do withdrawals work?",
                "q5a":  "Submit a withdrawal request from the Withdraw page. An admin reviews and approves each request manually before funds are sent.",
                "q6":  "What happens if a shared pool doesn't fill?",
                "q6a":  "Your contribution stays reserved in the filling pool. You can track progress on your dashboard. Once the pool reaches 100%, mining starts automatically for all contributors."
            },
